articles.title: US booze exports to Canada plunge more than 60% as fury over Trump tariffs sparks boycott
articles.description: Distilled Spirits Council says exports of US-made liquored totaled just $43.4 million during first six months of 2025, compared to about $114 million during the same period last year.
articles.content:
Boycott, eh? 
US exports of liquor and wine to Canada have plummeted by more than 60% in the first half of the year as furious Canucks snub American booze because of President Trump’s trade war.
